Episodes.Title: Tricks of the Trade
Episodes.Plot: Dog tries to trick fugitive by making an appointment after discovering that she is working for an escort service.
Episodes.ParentalRatingReason: M Offensive language and drug references

Episodes.Title: Jack & Jill (1)
Episodes.Plot: Dog visits the home of a couple of brother and sister fugitives as the begin tracking. Dog's instinct tells him not to believe the kid's mother when she says she has not seen them recently.

Episodes.Title: Jack & Jill (2)
Episodes.Plot: The Chapman kids have some new bunnies and Dog shows them how to care for them properly, followed by pursuing a suspect in a case of animal cruelty.

Episodes.Title: Island Hopper
Episodes.Plot: Dog helps a fellow bondsman when a fugitive from Washington state comes to Hawaii for a vacation.

Episodes.Title: Nice Guys Finish Last
Episodes.Plot: Dog offers his help to a fellow bondsman in searching for a fugitive, which is made harder due to his lack of knowledge of the suspect.

Episodes.Title: No Fly Zone
Episodes.Plot: Dog and his team must race against the airport when a fugitive is found to have booked a flight to Florida.

Episodes.Title: Teaching Moment
Episodes.Plot: Dog takes his son-in-law Travis on his first hunt after he makes a mistake and signs off on a fugitive's questionable bond.

Episodes.Title: Mission of Mercy
Episodes.Plot: Dog helps out a fellow bondsman who is grieving from recently losing his spouse, and learns that the fugitive has also just lost someone he loved.

Episodes.Title: Practice Makes Perfect
Episodes.Plot: Duane Lee receives an ample amount of criticism from Beth and must deal in a long search as a felon eludes him.

Episodes.Title: Save The Dogs
Episodes.Plot: Dog shows his kids the proper way to care for their new pet bunny rabbit, and then is sent to find a fugitive who was wanted for animal cruelty.

Episodes.Title: Back Behind Bars
Episodes.Plot: Dog shows his kids the proper way to care for their new pet bunny rabbit, and then is sent to find a fugitive who was wanted for animal cruelty.

Episodes.Title: Family Man
Episodes.Plot: It may be Dog's birthday but he is still on a case as a family is torn apart by drug addiction.

Episodes.Title: All in the Family
Episodes.Plot: Leland gets a hand from Dog as he hunts down a pair of mother and daughter fugitives.

Episodes.Title: Mother Courage (1)
Episodes.Plot: Dog knows that crime and drugs not only damage victims but also harm the families of the perpetrators, especially the kids. And both of the fugitives he's chasing today have left shattered families and struggling women in their wake. The challenge for Dog and the team--can they convince these women to help Dog track down their men?

Episodes.Title: Mother Courage (2)
Episodes.Plot: Dog and his team plan to capture Marco by using fellow fugitive Elizabeth.

Episodes.Title: Bounty Boot Camp (1)
Episodes.Plot: Dog loves a challenge and to help a friend. Today his friend Jim, a fellow bondsman, has asked Dog to help track down a dangerous fugitive and bring along his son, who is just learning the business himself. The hunt starts at a den which is filled with swords and knives. Before this day is over, doors will be kicked in, mace will be sprayed and one bounty hunter in training will be that much wiser.

Episodes.Title: Bounty Boot Camp (2)
Episodes.Plot: Dog and the posse help Leland track down a small-time Bonnie and Clyde couple.

Episodes.Title: Friends and Neighbors (1)
Episodes.Plot: Dog and his crew head to Colorado where he hunts down a fugitive drug dealer who's been running for six months now.

Episodes.Title: Friends and Neighbors (2)
Episodes.Plot: Dog hunts for a stripper that has gone on the lam.

Episodes.Title: The Set-Up (1)
Episodes.Plot: Darkness has fallen, but Dog is hot on the trail and he and his posse refuse to let up. They're searching for Marco, a "Big Fish" drug dealer who has a large bond due. The best way to catch them is through another fugitive, Elizabeth. Can Dog trick her into giving up her best friend? And what will Dog do when he finds out that the bait in the set-up is also a wanted man?

Episodes.Title: The Set-Up (2)
Episodes.Plot: Lyssa's wedding is only three days away, but a hot jump has Dog itching for the hunt.

Episodes.Title: The Searchers (1)
Episodes.Plot: Dog and the crew are still in Colorado where they are pursuing Marco. They suddenly receive a tip which sends them speeding south of Pueblo to meet with a longtime associate of Marco's.

Episodes.Title: The Searchers (2)
Episodes.Plot: They say you can't teach an old dog new tricks, but what if it's The Dog doing the teaching?

Episodes.Title: Buddha's Delight (1)
Episodes.Plot: Leland gets help on the Big Island from Dog and the posse as he hunts down a small-time Bonnie and Clyde couple. Their crime: stealing, including a pair of Buddha statues for resale. But the couple has deeper problems than this, which is revealed on the ride to the jail, and it's not a pretty picture.
